subcellularLocation.summary: Mainly localized to vesicles. In addition localized to the nucleus and centrosomes.

tissueExpression.summary: Skeletal and smooth muscle cells displayed strong cytoplasmic immunoreactivity. Heart myocytes were moderately stained. Remaining normal tissues were negative.
Malignant cells in general were negative.
Normal tissues displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity. Bile ducts, ovary and smooth muscle cells were weakly stained or negative.
Malignant cells displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity. Several cases of malignant melanoma, skin and lung cancers were negative.
